  "summary": "Main\nBy Jeffrey Landsberg\nThe most recent breakdown of China's coal imports by source has shown that September saw China's coal imports from Indonesia total 21.3 million tons. This is up from August by 1 million tons (5%) and is up year-on-year by 3.2 million tons (18%). Indonesia remains China's primary source of coal imports.",
